##

EXAMPLE: tests/grouped_expressions_in_array.stult

This example checks that an array may begin with a grouped expression.

A brace literal beginning with "{ (" should not automatically be treated as a
function literal. If the contents do not form a valid function literal, the
parser should parse the brace literal as an array.

##

WRITE_LINE : STD["IO"]["OUTPUT"]["WRITE_LINE"]
STRING_NEW : STD["TYPE"]["STRING"]["NEW"]
SIZE : STD["TYPE"]["COLLECTION"]["SIZE"]

A : 2
B : 3
C : 4

VALUES : {
	(A + B)
	((A + B) * C)
	(C - A)
}

WRITE_LINE("array size: " + STRING_NEW(SIZE(VALUES)))
WRITE_LINE("first: " + STRING_NEW(VALUES[0]))
WRITE_LINE("second: " + STRING_NEW(VALUES[1]))
WRITE_LINE("third: " + STRING_NEW(VALUES[2]))